[32m│[0m - Simple integer IDs are predictable and easily enumerable                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Security implications:**                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Broken Access Control**: Any unauthenticated user can access any        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m company's job listings                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Data Leakage**: Sensitive information (FLAG in Company 2) exposed via   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m IDOR                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Enumeration Risk**: All company IDs 1-10 are valid and accessible       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **No Rate Limiting**: Full enumeration completed without restrictions     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Recommended mitigations:**                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Implement proper authorization checks (verify user has access to requested [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m company)                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Use non-sequential, unpredictable identifiers (UUIDs)                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Add authentication requirements for sensitive endpoints                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Implement rate limiting to prevent mass enumeration                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Apply principle of least privilege (users should only see their own        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m company data)                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **This is a high-severity vulnerability** - The FLAG demonstrates that       [32m│[0m
