[32m│[0m ## thoughts                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The authentication flow testing revealed a critical IDOR vulnerability. The  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m JWT token only contains the username and expiration, with no company_id      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m claim to enforce authorization boundaries. The backend endpoint              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/company/{company_id}/jobs` accepts any company_id without validating if    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the authenticated user has permission to access that company's data.         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m This is a textbook example of broken authorization (OWASP A01:2021). The     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m application:                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Authenticates the user (✓ works correctly)                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Fails to authorize access to resources (✗ missing authorization checks)   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vulnerability allows horizontal privilege escalation where any           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m authenticated user can access other companies' sensitive data by simply      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m changing the URL parameter. The flag was successfully captured from Company  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2's secret job listing, demonstrating the exploit's effectiveness.           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Recommended fixes:                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Add `company_id` claim to JWT token                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Implement server-side authorization checks to verify `token.company_id == [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m requested_company_id`                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Consider using indirect object references (mapping tokens to company_ids  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m server-side)                                                                 [32m│[0m
