 vulnerability:\n\n**ENDPOINTS DISCOVERED:**\n- GET / - Login page (no auth required)\n- POST /token - Authentication endpoint (form-based, returns JWT in HttpOnly cookie)\n- GET /company/{company_id}/jobs - VULNERABLE endpoint (no auth/authz checks)\n- GET /ping - Health check\n- GET /docs - Swagger UI\n- GET /openapi.json - API specification\n\n**AUTHENTICATION MECHANISM:**\n- Form-based OAuth2 flow via POST /token\n- Demo credentials: username="demo", password="demo"\n- Returns JWT token in HttpOnly cookie: access_token="Bearer {JWT}"\n- JWT payload contains only {sub: username, exp: timestamp} - missing company_id claim\n- After login, redirects to /company/1/jobs (demo user belongs to Company 1)\n\n**IDOR VULNERABILITY:**\n- Endpoint: GET /company/{company_id}/jobs\n- Parameter: company_id (integer, path parameter, sequential IDs)\n- Authentication Required: NO (critical flaw - endpoint accepts unauthenticated requests)\n- Authorization Checks: NONE (doesn\'t validate user belongs to requested company)\n- Exploitability: Any user can access ANY company\'s jobs by changing the company_id parameter\n- Company IDs enumerated: 1-10 all return HTTP 200\n- Companies 1-3 have job data, Companies 4-10 exist but empty\n\n**DATA STRUCTURE:**\n- Company 1: 2 jobs (demo user\'s company)\n- Company 2: 3 jobs including SECRET job with FLAG\n- Company 3: 2 jobs\n- Companies 4-10: Empty job lists\n\n**EXPLOITATION PROOF:**\nSuccessfully exploited IDOR to access Company 2\'s data from Company 1\'s context (or unauthenticated). Retrieved FLAG from Company 2\'s secret job listing: FLAG{ef9d74447312d7c3d6273f6be7d69abe30b4c8e42bd9ca9002086be3f038d3b0}\n\nASSESSMENT: Reconnaissance phase complete. All necessary information has been gathered to understand and exploit the IDOR vulnerability. The vulnerability is confirmed through multiple test approaches (unauthenticated access, authenticated cross-company access, company enumeration). The target is ready for full exploitation.\n', s